From bfd7ac040ba9628b161d983feba38ef10affb6a7 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: lumaparallax <257510328+lumaparallax@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 9 Apr 2026 20:15:23 +0900
Subject: [PATCH 10/16] plugins: Drop obs-mediacodec

True zero-copy hardware encoding is not feasible within the Termux environment. Since we are forced to rely on CPU readback to cross the API boundaries, the standard FFmpeg encoders are significantly better optimized for this workflow. Removing this failed experimental implementation.
